userdoc.notice: Smart contract library of mathematical functions operating with signed 64.64-bit fixed point numbers.  Signed 64.64-bit fixed point number is basically a simple fraction whose numerator is signed 128-bit integer and denominator is 2^64.  As long as denominator is always the same, there is no need to store it, thus in Solidity signed 64.64-bit fixed point numbers are represented by int128 type holding only the numerator.

nodes.documentation:
Smart contract library of mathematical functions operating with signed
64.64-bit fixed point numbers.  Signed 64.64-bit fixed point number is
basically a simple fraction whose numerator is signed 128-bit integer and
denominator is 2^64.  As long as denominator is always the same, there is no
need to store it, thus in Solidity signed 64.64-bit fixed point numbers are
represented by int128 type holding only the numerator.
nodes.name: ABDKMath64x64

nodes.documentation:
Convert signed 256-bit integer number into signed 64.64-bit fixed point
number.  Revert on overflow.

   * @param x signed 256-bit integer number
@return signed 64.64-bit fixed point number
nodes.name: fromInt

nodes.documentation:
Convert signed 64.64 fixed point number into signed 64-bit integer number
rounding down.

   * @param x signed 64.64-bit fixed point number
@return signed 64-bit integer number
nodes.name: toInt

nodes.documentation:
Convert unsigned 256-bit integer number into signed 64.64-bit fixed point
number.  Revert on overflow.

   * @param x unsigned 256-bit integer number
@return signed 64.64-bit fixed point number
nodes.name: fromUInt

nodes.documentation:
Convert signed 64.64 fixed point number into unsigned 64-bit integer
number rounding down.  Revert on underflow.

   * @param x signed 64.64-bit fixed point number
@return unsigned 64-bit integer number
nodes.name: toUInt

nodes.documentation:
Convert signed 128.128 fixed point number into signed 64.64-bit fixed point
number rounding down.  Revert on overflow.

   * @param x signed 128.128-bin fixed point number
@return signed 64.64-bit fixed point number
nodes.name: from128x128

nodes.documentation:
Convert signed 64.64 fixed point number into signed 128.128 fixed point
number.

   * @param x signed 64.64-bit fixed point number
@return signed 128.128 fixed point number
nodes.name: to128x128
